…Says, ‘He’s recuperating fast’ …As President urges more support for Osinbajo From: Juliana Taiwo-Obalonye, Abuja Wife of the President, Mrs. Aisha Buhari, Tuesday morning, returned alone from the United Kingdom, where she has gone  to visit her husband, who is on medical leave Mrs. Buhari who left the country exactly a week ago (May 30th) 23 days after her husband left for further medical consultations, said she went to spend some time with her husband. “Her Excellency will spend some time with her Husband the President Muhammadu Buhari who is presently on medical vacation,” the one paragraph statement had read. Mrs. Buhari, on arrival Tuesday, conveyed the appreciation of the President to Nigerians over their constant prayers and said he will soon be with them as he is recuperating fast. She called on Nigerians to continue to be strong in the face of challenges and to support the Federal Government in implementing the agenda for which they were elected. In a statement by her Director of Information, Suleiman Haruna, she is quoted as saying “Mr. President thanked the acting President, Prof. Yemi Osinbajo for his loyalty and called on Nigerians to continue to support the acting President in his effort to actualize the mandate of the All Progressives’ Congress (APC).”